### Extension Functions in Kotlin

Extension functions allow you to add new functionality to existing classes without inheriting from them.

---

### Basic Extension Function Syntax

```kotlin
fun ReceiverType.extensionName(): ReturnType {
    // body using 'this' to access the receiver
}
```

---

### Example: String Extensions

```kotlin
fun String.addExclamation(): String = this + "!"

fun String.isEmail(): Boolean {
    return this.contains("@") && this.contains(".")
}

fun main() {
    println("Hello".addExclamation())  // Hello!
    println("test@test.com".isEmail())  // true
}
```

---

### Example: Int Extensions

```kotlin
fun Int.isEven(): Boolean = this % 2 == 0
fun Int.isPrime(): Boolean {
    if (this < 2) return false
    for (i in 2..this / 2) {
        if (this % i == 0) return false
    }
    return true
}

fun main() {
    println(4.isEven())   // true
    println(7.isPrime())  // true
}
```

---

### Extension Properties

You can also add properties to existing classes (but no backing fields).

```kotlin
val String.isNumeric: Boolean
    get() = this.all { it.isDigit() }

val <T> List<T>.secondOrNull: T?
    get() = if (size >= 2) this[1] else null

fun main() {
    println("12345".isNumeric)  // true
    println(listOf(1, 2, 3).secondOrNull)  // 2
}
```

---

### Extensions with Nullable Receivers

```kotlin
fun String?.isNullOrBlank(): Boolean {
    return this == null || this.isBlank()
}

println(null.isNullOrBlank())  // true
println("  ".isNullOrBlank())  // true
```

---

### Generic Extensions

```kotlin
fun <T> List<T>.customPrint(): String {
    return this.joinToString(" | ")
}

println(listOf(1, 2, 3).customPrint())  // 1 | 2 | 3
```

---

### Companion Object Extensions

```kotlin
class MyClass {
    companion object {}
}

fun MyClass.Companion.greet() = "Hello from companion!"

println(MyClass.greet())  // Hello from companion!
```

> **Key Point:** Extension functions are resolved statically based on the declared type, not the runtime type. They do not actually modify the original class.

